title: Dutch Oven Southwestern Chicken Pot Pie

ingredients.original_name: 1 pound skinless, boneless chicken breast, diced
ingredients.en_name: 1 Pound Skinless, Boneless Chicken Breast, Diced

ingredients.original_name: 1 (15 ounce) can diced tomatoes with green chiles, undrained
ingredients.en_name: 1 (15 ounces) Can Diced Tomatoes with Green Chiles, Undrained

ingredients.original_name: 2 (15 ounce) cans black beans, drained and rinsed
ingredients.en_name: 2 (15 ounces) Cans Black Beans, Drained and Rinsed

ingredients.original_name: salt and ground black pepper to taste
ingredients.en_name: Salt and Ground Black Pepper Two Taste

ingredients.original_name: 1 (8.5 ounce) package dry corn muffin mix
ingredients.en_name: 1 (8.5 ounces) Package Dry Corn Muffin Mix

instructions:
1. PREHEAT THE OUTSIDE TO 400 Degrees F (200 Degrees C).
2nd Heat Oil in a Dutch above Medium Heat. Add Chicken. Cook, Stirring Occasionally, Until No Longer Pink Inside, 5 Two 7 Minutes. Add Carrots, Celery, Bell Pepper, and Scallions and Cook Until Tender, About 5 Minutes. Add Tomatoes, Black Beans, Chili Powder, Cumin, Garlic, Onion Powder, Paprika, Salt, and Black Pepper. Stir two Combine. Cook Until Heated Through, About 5 Minutes More.
3.
4th Remove Dutch above From Heat and Spread Cornbread Batter on Top of Chicken Mixture to Form The Crust.
5. Place dutch above in the preheated above and bake Until cornbread is golden and beginning to brown, 20 two 25 minutes.
